Uses of Package
SwissCheese.annotations

  • Packages that use SwissCheese.annotations 
    Package Description
    SwissCheese.engine.camera
    Package for camera
    SwissCheese.engine.display
    Package for objects relating to display and ui when the 3D game is running.
    SwissCheese.engine.io.gson
    Package for classes and objects relating to input and output of JSON code through the GSON library.
    SwissCheese.engine.io.images
    Package for classes and objects relating to input and output of images used in Swiss Cheese game.
    SwissCheese.engine.keyboard
    Package for key listener class for the game.
    SwissCheese.engine.keyboard.keyActions
    Package for key actions for the game.
    SwissCheese.engine.texture
    Package for classes relating to any in-game textures
    SwissCheese.game
    The main game loop for Swiss Cheese game
    SwissCheese.gameSaving
    This package contains classes required for saving and serializing game saves to files.
    SwissCheese.map
    Package containing the map and other related objects and classes of the Swiss Cheese Game.
    SwissCheese.math
    This package contains objects that are to be used in Swiss Cheese math.
    SwissCheese.settings
    Package for Objects responsible for setting and saving game settings into SwissCheese/settings folder.
    SwissCheese.texturePacks
    This package contains classes relating to texture-packs used in the game.
    SwissCheese.uiWindows
    This package contains all classes for Swing windows of the user interface (such as menus).
